        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 5:03PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 502 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Lake Eaton Campground to near Eighth Lake
Campground. Movement was northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Indian Lake, Speculator, Blue Mountain Lake, Lake Durant Campground,
Long Lake, Eagle Nest, Sagamore Lake, Catlin Lake, Deerland, and Kamp
Kill Kare.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
these storms pass.</instruction>
